          "Eye Tracking Device, ILS Questionnaires",
          "Felder Silverman Learning Style Model (FSLSM)",
          "[Fixation, Whole Fixation, Visit, Glance, Total Duration, Modiefied Total Duration, Number, Modified Number, Time to First, Duration of First, Minimum/Average/Maximum duration, Last AOI viewed]",
          "Surveys reveal target while eye-tracking dimensions wiill be used as features… eacxh element on the LMS is mapped to an AOI Grouping: Table of Contents, Summary, Illustrations, Keywords, Theory, Exercise, Example, Supporting Text, MCQ, Additional Materials.\n\nOutliers were removed. Authors, in fact, do different pre-processings and test the different preprocessings on different algorithms.\n\n",
          "Logistic Regression, Ridge Regression, Decision Tree, RRandom Forest, Gradient Boosting, Naive Bayes, kNN, SVM, k-Means and MLP",
          "{Mean Accuracy: 0.69 - Gradient Boosting with ISF outlier removal and VAT feature Selection, F1-Score: 0.56 - NB with Mean imputation, LOF, Standard Scaler and VAT feature selection}",
          "-",
          "-",
          "The results show that predicting learning styles from eye-tracking alone is challenging, but the introduction of pre-processing steps seems to improve model performance. \n\n",
          "Authors attempt to use supervised Learning to predict each of the 4 dimensions FSLSM. To do that, the authors use the ILS survey for the target variables and test different algorithm/preprocessing configurations. \n\nResults show that ML from Eye Tracking is not particularly effective since iit does not achieve an average F1-Score of 0.8 (the author’s established target).",
          "- Limitations inherent to eye tracking tool or action classification.\n\n- No hyper-parameter tuning.\n\n- No data augmentation techniques used."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
